    "summary": "Mapped Agility CMS’s developer surface: 3 HTTP APIs (Content Fetch, Content Sync, Content Management), 1 GraphQL API, 2 MCP servers (1 OAuth-protected CMS server and 1 public docs server), and the Agility CLI, with API keys, PATs, CLI login, and MCP OAuth identified.",
    "credentials": {
      "fetch_api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "Fetch/Preview API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://manager.agilitycms.com/",
        "setup": "In Agility CMS, go to **Settings → API Keys** in your instance dashboard to view or create API keys. Choose the key type that matches the API surface you will call: `fetch` for published content or `preview` for staging/preview content. The docs say these keys can be added, edited, enabled/disabled, and deleted from that page. See [Content Fetch API](https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/content-fetch-api) and [GraphQL API](https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/graphql-api)."
      },
      "pat": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Personal Access Token",
        "generateUrl": "https://mgmt.aglty.io/index.html",
        "setup": "Create and manage PATs using the **Personal Access Tokens** section of the [Management API Swagger docs](https://mgmt.aglty.io/index.html). The docs state PATs are created by a user already authenticated via OAuth, are shown only once at creation, inherit the creating user's permissions, can be revoked, and are recommended for automation/CI. See [Personal Access Tokens - Public Beta](https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/personal-access-tokens-public-beta)."
      },
      "cli_oauth_login": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "CLI browser login session",
        "generateUrl": "https://manager.agilitycms.com/",
        "setup": "Install the CLI, then run `agility login`. The CLI opens a browser window for authentication and authorization, then stores the resulting session for subsequent CLI commands. See [CLI - Push / Pull / Clone](https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/cli)."
      },
      "mcp_oauth": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Agility CMS MCP OAuth authorization",
        "generateUrl": "https://mcp.agilitycms.com",
        "setup": "Connect your MCP client to the Agility CMS MCP endpoint and complete the built-in OAuth 2.0 authorization flow offered by Agility. The docs identify the MCP server as OAuth 2.0 protected and link to the one-click install/docs site at [mcp.agilitycms.com](https://mcp.agilitycms.com). See [Agility CMS MCP Server](https://agilitycms.com/docs/developers/agility-cms-mcp-server)."
      }
